In this article, President Trump welcomes the 2018 Stanley Cup Champions, the Washington Capitals, to the White House. He praises the team and its owner, Ted Leonsis, for their success. Trump specifically highlights team captain Alex Ovechkin, who had an impressive season and was named the playoff MVP. The President also mentions other players, such as John Carlson and Evgeny Kuznetsov, who made significant contributions to the team's victory. Trump expresses his confidence in the Capitals' ability to succeed in the upcoming playoffs and wishes them luck.